  "body": "Why in\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/utils/Multicall.sol\r\nyou don't copy the revert message as e.g. UniSwap do\r\nhttps://github.com/Uniswap/v3-periphery/blob/main/contracts/base/Multicall.sol\r\n\r\n            if (!success) {\r\n                // Next 5 lines from https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/a/83577\r\n                if (result.length < 68) revert();\r\n                assembly {\r\n                    result := add(result, 0x04)\r\n                }\r\n                revert(abi.decode(result, (string)));\r\n            }\r\n\r\nI think this is useful and expected behaviour",
