    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @vsmelov \r\n\r\n`Multicall` uses `Address.functionDelegateCall` which in turn calls `Address.verifyCallResult`. This means that if the delegate call fails, and if this failure comes with a reason, then the reason is bubbled. The `errorMessage` is just a fallback in case the delegateCall faills with no data.\r\n\r\n",
